
// The code schedules a task to be executed on the first day of every month at 5 AM UTC. The [tasks.schedule] slot is used to define the schedule for the task with ID "task-id-xyx". The [repeats] pattern "**.01.05.00.00" specifies that the task should repeat every month on the first day at 5 AM. The double asterisks (**) indicate that the task should run every month.
tasks.schedule:task-id-xyx
   repeats:**.01.05.00.00
